<HEADLINE>
KLEINE CONTACTED ABOUT JOB 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By BOB YOUNG  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Suns center  &UR; Joe Kleine said Tuesday he has been contacted by
Arkansas-Little Rock about the school's vacant Division I
basketball coaching position.
</P>
<P>
   Kleine, who played collegiately in nearby Fayetteville for
Arkansas, confirmed Arkansas-Little Rock Athletic Director  &UR; Rick
Mello has contacted him to determine whether Kleine has interest in
the job. It opened earlier this month when  &UR; Wimp Sanderson
resigned.
</P>
<P>
   And Kleine is giving it consideration.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're in the process of talking about it,'' Kleine said. ``I
don't know where it's going to lead.''
</P>
<P>
   Kleine, a veteran of 14 NBA seasons, said he hasn't decided yet
whether he wants to continue his playing career beyond this season.
He signed a one-year contract with the Suns for $1 million, the
minimum a veteran of 10 seasons or more can receive.
</P>
<P>
   If Arkansas-Little Rock were to offer Kleine the job, and if he
were to accept it, he would complete the season with the Suns.
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans play in the Sun Belt Conference and finished 12-15
last season. Reportedly,  &UR; Scott Edgar, a former Arkansas assistant
and former Duquesne head coach, also is a candidate. &QL; 
In reserve &QL; 
Guard  &UR; Rex Chapman rarely has come off the bench during his playing
career and said he doesn't remember being very good at it. But
Chapman said he's willing to accept that role.
</P>
<P>
   He came off the bench Tuesday night against the Milwaukee Bucks
for the second game in a row behind rookie  &UR; Toby Bailey.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've got to do whatever we can do to win some ballgames,''
Chapman said. ``I'm willing to try anything.
</P>
<P>
   ``I haven't done it in so long, but you just try to get used to
it. You try to find the flow of the game sitting over there and be
ready when it's your turn.''
</P>
<P>
   Chapman played 27 minutes in reserve Tuesday night, hitting 5 of
10 shots, including three of his four three-point attempts, and
scoring 13 points.
</P>
<P>
   Wednesday, against the Hornets, Chapman compiled a season-high
25 points on eight-of-18 shooting and was three of seven from
three-point range. &QL; 
They said it &QL;
</P>
<P>
   In the fourth quarter Tuesday, a fan asked referee  &UR; Dick Bavetta
to count a basket that had been waved off for the Bucks.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'll give you a first-class upgrade,'' the fan yelled, in
reference to the scandal that saw several veteran NBA officials
dismissed, and later reinstated, because they didn't claim income
from airline ticket exchanges on their taxes.
</P>
<P>
   Showing a sense of humor, Bavetta, who wasn't among the referees
implicated, wheeled to the scorer's table and said, ``Let's score
those two points.'' &QL; 
No surprise &QL; 
Suns forward  &UR; Tom Gugliotta wasn't surprised when the Minnesota
Timberwolves traded  &UR; Stephon Marbury because the club wasn't going
to be able to re-sign him.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought that might happen,'' said Gugliotta, who has denied
assertions that he and Marbury did not get along. ``I never had a
problem with Stephon. He created a lot of the offense I got there.
He talked a lot about going to a big market where there are more
opportunities for endorsements.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
