Michelangelo, we understand little about the man. In ``Three Worlds
of Michelangelo,'' James H. Beck reaches the quality that lies
behind both his life and his work - his humanity. Patricia Fortini
Brown reviews this biography of Michelangelo and the men who
influenced him. 1,500 words. B. GOING HOME An Iranian-American
woman returns and discovers a Teheran full of contradictions. In
``To See and See Again : A Life in Iran and America,'' Tara
Bahrampour has written a fascinating, often moving, account of her
life on the boundary between two very different cultures. Review by
Adrienne Edgar. 1,500 words. 
