<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   OLY-IOC-REFORMS _ LAUSANNE, Switzerland _ Trying to put its
worst scandal behind it and make sure is doesn't happen again, the
IOC today adopted the first planks in a reform platform aimed at
soothing powerful critics and assuring it's up to date for the next
millennium. It agreed to choose the site of the 2006 Winter
Olympics from two finalists, leaving its rank-and-file with one of
the few actions it takes but putting strict limits on their contact
with bidders. (Roughton, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (i) International and (s) Sports categories.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   OLY-IOC-MONEY _ LAUSANNE, Switzerland _ IOC discloses perks for
IOC members and salaries for staffers. (Roughton/Turner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (i) International and (s) Sports categories.
</P>
<P>
   OLY-SCALLY _ ATLANTA _ The Salt Lake Olympic bid group sent
$14,500 in 23 separate checks to Atlantan Raouf Scally, whom it
believed was related to Algerian IOC member Mohamed Zerguini. Turns
out, he is the grandson of the late Hadj Mohammed Benjoullen of
Morocco, who died two years ago. Scally's uncle is Atlanta
restarateur Rafih Benjelloun, who had plenty of contacts with
Olympic people but said Scally did not. (Fish, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 40.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (i) International and (s) Sports categories.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON/POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   DISABLED _ WASHINGTON _ The President's Committee on the
Employment of People With Disabilities announces on Thursday a
program to help find jobs for graduating college seniors with
disabilities. (Mollison, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   NURSING-HOMES _ WASHINGTON _ An investigation of nursing homes
in Texas, Pennsylvania, California and Michigan concluded that many
have life-threatening violations of health and safety standards.
Complaints against nursing homes have a 700 case backlog amid signs
that conditions are worsening. (Malone, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   QUACKERY _ WASHINGTON _ James Randi, better known as the
magician ``the Amazing Randi,'' appears at an event to debunk
pseudoscience in popular culture sponsored by bipartisan members of
the House Science Committee. (Nesmith, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   RACISM _ WASHINGTON _ Rep. Robert Wexler, D-Fla., joins
prominent black and Hispanic Congress members to discuss a House
resolution ``condemning the racism and bigotry'' of the Council of
Conservative Citizens. (Lipman, Cox News Serviice)..
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   GRADSKOL-RANKING _ U.S. News releases rankings of America's best
graduate schools. (Suggs, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   TIGERS _ Tiger Haven in Roan County, Tenn., is being forced to
move because of protests from scared neighbors and zoning
violations. (Harmon, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-HEALTHCARE _ Gov. George W. Bush earned praise two years
ago for extending food stamps to legal immigrants even after the
federal government cut them off. But he may be taking a different
approach on a children's health insurance program. Bush would
exclude recent immigrant children from the soon-to-be-launched
Children's Health Insurance Program. It's sure to be seen as a test
of compassion versus conservatism. (Greenberger, Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
