<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HAVE YOUR CAKE AND READ ITS HISTORY, TOO
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: What is the history of wedding cakes?
</P>
<P>
   _ A.B., Issaquah, Wash.
</P>
<P>
   A: Wedding cakes began in ancient Greece as hard biscuits that
were crumbled atop the bride's head by guests.
</P>
<P>
   This was supposed to ensure fertility, Arlene Stewart writes in
``A Bride's Book of Wedding Traditions.'' Romans expanded the
tradition by eating these crumbs.
</P>
<P>
   Stewart writes that during the 17th century, a French chef used
icing to hold a stack of these biscuits together, creating the
tradition of the tiered wedding cake.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Victorians introduced the white three-tiered cake balanced
on columns that is still the most common style seen today,'' writes
another Stewart, Martha, in Newsday.
</P>
<P>
   One tradition that appears less frequently is a groom's cake,
served at the reception or handed out in slices to departing
guests.
</P>
<P>
   ``There is a legend that if a single woman goes to sleep with a
slice of groom's cake beneath her pillow, she will dream of her
future husband,'' Martha Stewart writes.
</P>
<P>
   Q: How can I contact Louis Gossett Jr.?
</P>
<P>
   _ E.R., Hurst, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to him in care of Logo Entertainments, 1888 Century
Park E., No. 1900, Los Angeles, CA 90067.
</P>
<P>
   Gossett is writing and directing segments for ``Love Songs,'' a
Showtime cable project that premieres April 25.
</P>
<P>
   The 62-year-old actor, who has appeared in several Showtime
films recently, was master of ceremonies at an October 1998 event
honoring departing Washington, D.C., Mayor Marion Barry.
</P>
<P>
   ``All during his low period is when I loved him the most,''
Gossett told the Miami Herald of Barry, who served a six-month
sentence on drug charges in the early '90s but managed a political
comeback and was re-elected mayor in 1994.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I find San Marcos brand lime chili chips?
</P>
<P>
   _ M.W., Grapevine, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: San Marcos tortilla chips, originally produced by C&AMP;C Bakery
of Kingsville, Texas, are now distributed by Bimbo Bakeries U.S.A.
</P>
<P>
   Bimbo, which also owns Mrs Baird's, sells ``megathin'' San
Marcos tortilla chips in the Austin, San Antonio, Houston and Rio
Grande areas.
</P>
<P>
   ``We don't have a lime and chili San Marcos chip,'' said Lucile
Crouch, the company's consumer relations coordinator.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-18-99 1547EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
