   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``w'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   PATIENT-RIGHTS (Washington) _ A Senate committee is expected to
approve a bill defining a wide range of new rights for patients,
after two days of intense conflict between Republicans and
Democrats over the proper role of the federal government in
regulating health insurance. The battle over an issue that stirs
more public interest than many issues before Congress is only the
first stage of a conflict likely to be continued into the 2000
elections. By Robert Pear.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL-GENERAL
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``a'' news file.)
