   MARIJUANA-GATEWAY (Undated) _ A government-commissioned report
on marijuana released on Wednesday focused on the drug's medicinal
uses, but outside the medical profession it was most closely read
for what it said about marijuana's central role in the nation's war
against illicit drugs. By Christopher S. Wren.
</P>
<P>
   FINANCIAL
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``f'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   TRADE-REPORT (Washington) As American exports continued to fall,
the United States trade deficit jumped to a new monthly record of
$17 billion in January, fueled by a flood of imports from China
that could stir further protectionist sentiments in Congress. Among
the imports that surged into the United States from China was a
huge increase in steel, and the protectionist movement may gain
momentum now that China joins Japan, Brazil and Russia on the list
of nations pouring inexpensive steel into the American market. By
David E. Sanger.
</P>
