<P>
   ASSISI-EXHIBIT (New York) _ To draw attention to the the
post-earthquake situation in Assisi, as well as to showcase a
remarkable body of art temporarily out of pubic view elsewhere, the
Metropolitan Museum collaborated with various Italian cultural
agencies and the Vatican to organize ``The Treasury of St. Francis
of Assisi,'' an exhibition of some 70 objects from the church's
holdings, supplemented by 30 related works from other collections.
By Holland Cotter.
