   MIDWEST REGIONAL
</P>
<P>
   BKC-MIAMI-MURNEN _ ST. LOUIS _ The Miami University basketball
players have dedicated this season to their team manager. Jay
Murnen, a Kettering, Ohio, native and Miami student, fell three
stories from a railing several years ago and was in a coma for
months. His younger borther, an Alter High School player, visited
him regularly and helped Murnen pull through. Jay recovered and
tried out for the Miami team. He was cut but took on the manager's
role. Earlier this month, the younger brother died of bone cancer
at age 19. Now, Wally Szczerbiak and the others say they want to
beat Kentucky in honor of this Kettering family. (Archdeacon,
Dayton Daily News). 30. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
