successful enough to reach the women's Sweet 16. But Kelly and Coco
Miller are just as emotional as they are talented and they have had
their share of emotional outbursts this season. Both players are
very hard on themselves and they aren't afraid to let the other
know about it. (Parker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   NCAA SWIMMING/DIVING CHAMPIONSHIPS
</P>
<P>
   SWM-NCAASWIM _ ATHENS, GA. _ Coverage of the NCAA women's
swimming and diving championships at the University of Georgia in
Athens. (Brice, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   SWM-SWIM-NOTES _ ATHENS, GA. _ Women's swimming and diving
notebook. (Brice/Towers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).10.
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL
</P>
<P>
   NFL
</P>
<P>
   FBN-OWNERS-NOTES _ PHOENIX _ NFL notebook wrapping up NFL owners
meetings. (Pasquarelli, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   OUTDOORS
</P>
<P>
   COANGLERS _ As the professional anglers on bass fishing's
richest tour fish Georgia's Lake Lanier this week for a $100,000
first prize, the amateurs or ``co-anglers'' will be along for the
ride. Amateur anglers who sign up for FLW Tour events don't find
out until the day before it starts whether they make it in by
lottery, and they are assigned to a pro's boat. From there on,
they're just along for the ride; the pro decides where they'll fish
and for how long. The folks who do this range from young hopefuls
to retirement-age folks like Judy and Abbie of Florida who follow
the tour all over the country. (Bernarde, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18-20. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
