<P>
   UNDATED _ Most people think of Michael Dell as one of the
wunderkinds of the personal computer business. Dell Computer Corp.,
launched from a dorm room at the University of Texas in 1983, has
grown into an industry powerhouse generating $18 billion in annual
revenues selling built-to-order PCs. In the process, the value of
the company's stock has risen faster than that of any other
publicly traded company during the past decade. What most people
are just beginning to realize, though, is that, unwittingly,
Michael Dell may well have been the Internet's first entrepreneur.
By TERESA MCUSIC. Story has moved in ``f'' financial category. &QL; 
