<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Whoopi and Oscar, together again tonight
 &HT;    EDs: Embargoed for Sunday, March 21.
 &HT;    Staff reports
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``THE 71ST ANNUAL ACADEMY AWARDS''
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Showtime: 8:30 tonight on ABC.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Host: Whoopi Goldberg.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Best song performers: Aerosmith (``I Don't Want to Miss a
Thing'' from ``Armageddon''); Celine Dion and Andrea Bocelli (``The
Prayer'' from ``Quest for Camelot''); Allison Moorer (``A Soft
Spot'' from ``The Horse Whisperer''); Randy Newman and Peter
Gabriel (``That'll Do'' from ``Babe: Pig in the City'') and Whitney
Houston and Mariah Carey (``When You Believe'' from ``The Prince of
Egypt'').
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Special Oscar: Elia Kazan. A controversial selection because
the director named names during the House Un-American Activities
Committee's infamous probe of Communists in Hollywood.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Irving G. Thalberg Award: Norman Jewison.
</P>
<P>
   THE PREVIEW SHOW
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Showtime: 8 p.m. on ABC.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Hosts: Geena Davis and CNN's Jim Moret.
