   KOSOVO-U.S. (Washington) _ With the Kosovo talks at a dead end
and Yugoslavia's Slobodan Milosevic more recalcitrant than ever,
the Clinton administration is faced with pushing forward on a
policy _ the NATO bombing of a sovereign country _ that its
officials have repeatedly said they really don't want to carry out.
By Jane Perlez.
