interest in a United States Senate seat from New York, Hillary
Rodham Clinton has discussed her potential candidacy with 60
influential Democrats, including the major party chairmen from the
suburban and upstate counties crucial to winning a race. Many
officials describe their conversations with the first lady as
lengthy and extraordinarily detailed about local issues. By
Elisabeth Bumiller.
