<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    UT board chairman re-elected
 &HT;    By Staff reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ Don Evans, recently named national finance
chairman of Gov. George W. Bush's presidential exploratory
committee, will continue to serve in another big volunteer job:
chairman of the UT System Board of Regents.
</P>
<P>
   The nine-member board unanimously elected Evans to a second
two-year term at a special meeting Thursday. The board also
re-elected vice chairmen Tom Loeffler of San Antonio and Rita
Crocker Clements of Dallas.
</P>
<P>
   Evans, who is 52 and has two degrees from UT, is president and
chief executive officer of an oil and gas company, Tom Brown Inc.
Evans told the board he was ``not only humbled but also flattered
that the board has placed their confidence in me once again. ... I
look forward to the next two years _ to making higher education
more accessible, more affordable to all Texans.''
</P>
<P>
   Evans said later that he would not have sought a second term if
he did not think he had the time to devote to it. He and his family
are considering moving to Austin, but no decision has been made, he
said.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
