<HEADER>
A5749 &Cx1f; ttd-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRO     03-18 0709
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AND NOW, A WORD FROM A NOMINEE
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Nick Nolte &LR; , nominated for a best-actor Oscar for his role in
``Affliction,'' told Playboy magazine that he's not a member of the
Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't like the concept, the competition, the picking of
actors for best performance of the year,'' said Nolte. ``You can't
make that kind of a judgment. It smacks of unfairness. It's
popularized and highly commercial.
</P>
<P>
   ``I have nothing against a group of actors getting together to
honor each other's good work for the year, but I'm really opposed
to allowing the whole world in on the process. I don't think you
can pick the best picture of the year, or the best actor.''
</P>
<P>
   He said Oscar season is ``a terrible time for this town. It's a
terrible time for the business. On the commercial side, it's a
great thing to expose millions of people to the film industry. But
everybody turns into a maniac. Everybody drops his persona and
becomes terribly greedy. They all are anyway, but it really comes
out at that time.''
</P>
<P>
   P.S. The Earth Island Institute's Green Screen Awards for best
environmental films of the year: ``A Civil Action,'' ``A Bug's
Life,'' ``Antz,'' ``Mighty Joe Young'' and ``The Avengers,''
wherein the villain's nefarious plot is to take control of the
weather.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DIRECTOR ON DIRECTOR &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Steven Spielberg &LR; , who has said he felt ``uncomfortable''
saying anything about ``Life Is Beautiful'' except ``I'm happy when
anyone makes a movie that says the Holocaust happened,'' didn't
much like the movie, says the New York Daily News.
</P>
<P>
   Spielberg's own ``Saving Private Ryan'' is competing with ``Life
Is Beautiful'' for best Oscar, but rivalry may not be the cause of
the director's disdain. He said in an interview several years back
that a Holocaust movie ``cannot in the least come across as
entertainment.''
</P>
<P>
   According to the Daily News, Spielberg wanted to leave the
theater in the middle of the Italian movie, but his wife told him
to stay put because leaving would ``send a bad message,'' a source
told the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE ADVENTURES OF HILLARY &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Hillary Clinton &LR; 's been spending a lot of time in New York,
apparently some portion of it exploring nonpolitical plans.
According to New York magazine, New York University's law school
has offered her an associate professorship.
</P>
<P>
   _ On March 3, the first lady attended an A-list dinner party at
the townhouse of former Deputy Treasury Secretary  &UR; Roger &LR; 
 &UR; Altman &LR; .  &UR; Lesley Stahl &LR;  and  &UR; Mort Zuckerman &LR;  were there, said New
York, as well as  &UR; Barry Diller &LR;  and Children's Television Workshop
founder  &UR; Joan Ganz Cooney &LR; , the latter two, as the invitation had
specified, without spouses or significant others.
</P>
<P>
   According to Altman's wife,  &UR; Jurate Kazickas &LR; , the invitations
were for one person because ``space was a consideration, and we
wanted as diverse a group as possible.''
</P>
<P>
   ``That seemed strange at first, when the invitation came,'' said
one person who was there. ``But it worked. It was a nice party.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Meanwhile, the first lady answered preset questions on
Tuesday's online ``chat'' to sell ``Dear Socks, Dear Buddy: Kids'
Letters to the First Pets.'' She ignored such questions as: ``Is
there no more on the minds of the American people than Socks and
Buddy? Please!'' and ``Socks got used to Buddy, so (can) you get
used to Monica?''
</P>
<P>
   One e-mailer, who had asked whether Mrs. Clinton's philosophy
had been influenced by John Denver, admonished the others: ``Please
have some respect, folks.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``This notice is for informational purposes only. No action is
required. To more effectively manage the bank's reserve
requirements, each checking account includes a savings subaccount.
The subaccount will be completely transparent to you and will not
affect any aspect of your relationship with the bank. ... If you
have any questions, please contact us.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Notice from Wells Fargo bank to account-holder W.N. Jayme, who
wrote right back to the bank manager telling him the exact same
thing, for informational purposes only.
</P>
