<P>
   (NYT5) NEW YORK -- March 18, 1999 -- THEATER-NOTES, 3-18 --
Kristine Nielsen in ``Betty's Summer Vacation.'' Besides the
general strain of playing a savage comedy eight times a week, the
play's subject matter - media, molestation and masculine mutilation
- hasn't sat well with some audience members. ``There are nights
where it is very quiet out there,'' she says. Thankfully, however,
those moments are broken by laughter, and often it is Ms. Nielsen
the audience has to thank. (Sara Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
