<HEADER>
A5915 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKC-FLORIDA-GONZAGA19     03-18 0423
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKC-FLORIDA-GONZAGA19-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Late put-back sends Gonzaga past Florida
 &HT;    By Len Pasquarelli
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX _ Casey Calvary's tip-in with 4.4 seconds remaining
helped Gonzaga continue its surprising tournament run Thursday with
a 73-72 victory over Florida in the West Regional semifinals.
</P>
<P>
   With the victory, Gonzaga (28-6) advances to Saturday's regional
final against the winner of the Connecticut-Iowa semifinal.
</P>
<P>
   Trailing 72-71 with less than 10 seconds remaining, Gonzaga's
Quentin Hall drove the lane and attempted a running jumper which
bounced high off the back of the rim. Calvary raced down the lane
and tapped in Hall's miss for the basket and the lead.
</P>
<P>
   Florida (22-9) had a chance to win the game, but Eddie Shannon
missed a 3-pointer from the right corner as time expired.
</P>
<P>
   Florida took its first lead, 39-37, just 59 seconds into the
second half when Kenyan Weaks stole the ball at the top of the key,
drove for a layup and was fouled. The advantage was short-lived,
however, as Gonzaga guard Richie Frahm tossed in a long
three-pointer to key a 12-3 run over the next six minutes. Calvary
helped establish an inside game with two rebound buckets and two
foul shots off a follow.
</P>
<P>
   The Gators used a 14-1 run late in the first half to overcome a
26-13 deficit and tie the game at 27, but still trailed 35-34 at
intermission. Given their sloppy play and inability to defend the
three-point shot, coach Billy Donovan's club was fortunate to be
within a single point.
</P>
<P>
   Gonzaga nailed seven of 12 3-pointers in the opening 20 minutes
but the Bulldogs' reliance on the trey also proved disastrous at
times. Three times they turned the ball over by trying to float
skip-passes over the Florida defense and the miscues led to two
easy baskets and a shooting foul for Florida.
</P>
<P>
   Especially sloppy for Gonzaga was point guard Quentin Hall,
whose three assists in the half were offset by five turnovers.
Shooting guard Matt Santangelo, the Bulldogs' best perimeter
player, mirrored his backcourt mate's inconsistency. After hitting
two treys in the opening five minutes, Gonzaga's sharpshooter
missed seven straight shots.
</P>
<P>
   The teams played poorly in the opening 10 minutes. Not
surprisingly, Donovan, whose team features 11 players averaging
over 10 minutes per game, tried to wear down a Gonzaga club with
only 10 players on its entire roster. Donovan made 24 substitutions
in the half.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
